  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<em>Your unarmed strike brings a revelation down upon your foe.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Revelation class feature, Improved Unarmed Strike.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>When you gain this feat, choose one revelation that you can use to affect no more than one opponent. If you make a successful unarmed strike against an opponent, in addition to dealing your unarmed strike damage, you can use a swift action to deliver the effects of the chosen revelation to that opponent. Doing so provokes no attacks of opportunity.<br/><br/><b>Special</b><br/>You can take this feat multiple times. Each time you take it, you apply it to a different qualifying revelation.<br/><br/><b>Combat Trick</b><br/>After hitting with an unarmed strike, you can spend 2 stamina points to apply the effects of your chosen revelation as a free action instead of a swift action. If the chosen revelation has unlimited daily uses, this combat trick costs 5 stamina points instead.",
